{
  "stem": "3022.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "Actually what we did was we had a clandestine radio.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "And we printed out on onion papers the messages that came from BBC, from London, where General Sikorski tried to, you know, to lift the spirits of the Polish population, the promising-- telling us about the news of, of the front.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "And also the Germans, in order to, to, to bring-- to take in the currency, they decided that they're going to stamp all the high denominations bills with a special stamp.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "And so-- and you had only a limited amount of money that they would stamp.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "If you had a lot of money, you know, you, you were just-- unless you had foreign currency, the money was worthless.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "So we falsified the stamp, and we used to stamp the money.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "And we also monitored people that used to work for the Germans, in case they were traitors.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "I understand that the two girls that used to work in one of the German barracks that the [INAUDIBLE] the Germans were eventually executed.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "But we had no way of knowing.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "The way the cells were arranged, there were four people in the cell.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "You only knew only one of the people in the cell, and you-- the people from the next cell.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "And the cell that I was in was my cousin, I, and two brothers, two Polish fellows by the name of [?",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 58,
      "text": "Konik. ?] And one time when I was transporting the onion papers with, with the news where there was a roundup.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 59,
      "text": "I was in a streetcar, and they rounded up-- they were taking people to labor, to Germany.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 60,
      "text": "And if I was found was that particularly newspaper with me-- you know, they were just one sheet.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 61,
      "text": "The news were on one sheet.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
